      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "It might be better to report the issue now (or to archive it), since the LibreLane branch is still in flux. As soon as I rebase `leo/gf180mcu`, you won't be able to fetch the same hash.\n\nYou can create a reproducible like so:\n\n- Enable the Nix shell\n- Start a run (there is a problem)\n- cd to `librelane/runs/<timestamp>/xx-your-step/`\n- Run: `librelane.steps create-reproducible` (This will create a LibreLane reproducible.)\n- cd into the created `reproducible` folder and run: `./run_ol.sh eject` (This will make the reproducible standalone.)\n- Compress the `reproducible` folder and use it to file an issue\n\nYou can reproduce the issue by running `./run.sh` inside `reproducible`.",
